# Main Idea + Key Details

Research consistently shows:

# Comprehension

improves when students learn to identify:

```text id="m7v3qe"
what the text is mostly about
```

and:

```text id="p2m8rt"
details that support meaning
```

Students learn:

```text id="x5v1qe"
read
→ identify topic
→ find important details
→ explain meaning
```

This develops:

* comprehension
* summarizing
* information filtering
* critical thinking

This becomes:

# Meaning Extraction

Children often remember details but miss the:

```text id="r8m4qe"
big idea
```

This skill teaches them to find both.

